article.headline: Tennessee State 74, Murray State 68
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Eric King scored a career-high 27 points to lead Tennessee State to a 74-68 victory over Murray State on Thursday night. The Tigers (12-15, 7-6 Ohio Valley Conference) shot 63.2 percent (12 of 19) in the second half to overcome a 37-35 halftime deficit. Bruce Price scored 23 points and Rod Flowers had 14 for Tennessee State, which stayed unbeaten at home in the OVC and snapped a 12-game losing streak against the Racers (14-10, 9-5) dating to 2000. Trey Pearson scored 19 points, including 4 of 4 from 3-point range, and Pearson Griffith had 14 points and nine rebounds for Murray State. Darnell Hopkins added 10 points, and Pearson also had seven assists. Tennessee State took a 58-48 lead with 8:53 to play after a Flowers layup, and the Tigers led by as much as 63-48 with 7:07 left. But Murray State roared back, going on a 20-6 run capped by a Hopkins layup with 1:18 to play to pull within 69-68. Flowers hit a layup and the Tigers hit enough free throws in the final minute to seal the win. Tennessee State finished shooting 56.5 percent from the floor and made 20 of 28 free throw attempts. Murray State shot 41.5 percent and was 8 of 12 from the charity strip. There were nine ties in the game.
